<h1>EARLY CANADIANA ONLINE TERMS OF SERVICE</h1>

<h3>GENERAL</h3>

<p>These are the Canadiana.org terms of service governing the use of the
Early Canadiana Online (ECO) web site. Canadiana.org reserves the right to
update these terms of service from time to time.</p>

<h3>USER ACCOUNTS AND PRIVACY</h3>

<p>In order to obtain a Canadiana user account, a valid e-mail address
must be provided. Canadiana.org will not share email addresses or account
information with third parties, except as required by law. Canadiana.org
will not send unsolicited email to email addresses provided by the user,
except for notices directly relating to account and subscription status
and related matters.</p>

<p>Canadiana.org retains the right to restrict, suspend or terminate user
accounts for behaviour that is abusive, illegal, or which unduly impairs
access for other users.</p>

<p>Canadiana.org logs information about use of the site. This information
may be shared in aggregate with third parties, but personally identifiable
information will not be disclosed except as required by law.</p>

<h3>USE OF THE SITE</h3>

<p>Users who are not subscribers to ECO have limited access to the its
content and features.  Subscribers and users accessing ECO from a location
covered by an institutional site license have access to all content and
features; however, access to certain features may require a valid
Canadiana user account.</p>

<p>Canadiana.org reserves the right to impose reasonable limits on an
individual's use of the site in order to maintain overall quality of
service. This includes but is not limited to restricting the number of
concurrent downloads from any one individual.</p>

<h3>SUBSCRIPTIONS</h3>

<p>Subscriptions are for the personal use of one individual or household.
Subscribers must not distribute their Canadiana account credentials and
must take reasonable care to ensure that their password remains
secure.</p>

<p>Subscribers may access all ECO content and features for the duration of
their subscription, and may download copies of any material in the
collection.  They may also continue to access and use
previously-downloaded materials (PDF documents) after their subscription
terminates; however, lost or destroyed copies cannot be re-downloaded
outside of the subscription period. It is the responsibility of the
subscriber to ensure proper storage and backup of any content downloaded
from the ECO site.</p>

<p>Subscribers agree to limit their use of ECO to reasonable personal use
(for any purpose, including academic and commercial). In particular,
subscribers agree not to systematically download, mirror, or otherwise
replicate substantial portions of the ECO collection.</p>

<p>Canadiana.org holds copyright to the ECO collection as a whole.
Substantial portions of the collection may not be reproduced or
distributed without its express permission.</p>


